SvakSvat uses Sphinx (sphinx.pocoo.org) for the documentation.

To build the documentation just run:
sphinx-build doc/source doc/build 
and open doc/build/index.html in your favorite browser.

Dependencies for SvakSvatGUI as Ubuntu packages:
python3-sqlalchemy
python3-pyqt4
python3-keyring
python3-psycopg2
python3-dbus (for SecretServiceKeyring)
ldap-utils (for LDAP support)
openssh-client (to perform SSH port forwarding)

To run on Ubuntu:
cp svaksvat.cfg.cp svaksvat.cfg
python3 svaksvatgui.py

To run svaksvat scripts:
ex.
python3 scripts/modulenadresser.py


Install on windows:

1. Install python3 from official website, and clone the Git Repo.
2. Install pip installer http://www.pip-installer.org/en/latest/installing.html
3. Add C:\python33 and C:\python33\Scripts (Dependent on your installation path) to the Path system variable. http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3701646/how-to-add-to-the-pythonpath-in-windows-7
4. Install PyQt4 http://www.riverbankcomputing.com/software/pyqt/download
5. Install psycopg2 http://www.stickpeople.com/projects/python/win-psycopg/
6. Open a command line, by pressing  windows+r buttons
7. Install following packages with pip by writing "pip install package_name". Replace package_name with sqlalchemy and keyring
8. Fix the config file.
9. Copypaste a putty.exe to the Svaksvat folder. http://www.putty.org/
